devdoc.details: This contract implements the VolatilePair interface and inherits from the PairERC20 contract. It also uses the Initializable contract from the OpenZeppelin library.

Burn(address,uint256,uint256,address).details: Emitted when liquidity is removed from the pool

params.to: The address that receives the tokens

ClaimFees(address,address,uint256,uint25.details: Emitted when admin fees are claimed

Mint(address,uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when liquidity is added to the pool

SetAdminFeeRate(uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when the admin fee rate is updated

SetSwapFeeRate(uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when the swap fee rate is updated

params.amount0In: The amount of token0 being swapped in
params.amount0Out: The amount of token0 being swapped out
params.amount1In: The amount of token1 being swapped in
params.amount1Out: The amount of token1 being swapped out
params.to: The address that receives the swapped tokens

SwapFee(address[],uint256[]).details: Emitted when the swap fee rate is updated

params.swapFees: The new swap fee rates for each token
params.tokens: The addresses of the tokens in the pair

Sync(uint112,uint112).details: Emitted when the reserves are synced

approve(address,uint256).details: Approves a spender to transfer tokens on behalf of the owner.

params.spender: The address of the spender to be approved.
params.value: The amount of tokens to be approved for transfer.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the approval was successful or not.

burn(address).details: Burn liquidity tokens from the caller and remove corresponding reserves

params._to: The address to send the tokens to

getAmountOut(address,address,uint256).details: Returns the amount of output tokens given an input amount of a token

params._amount: The input amount of the token
params._from: The address of the input token
params._to: The address of the output token

getRealBalanceOf().details: Returns the real balance of each token in the pair, excluding the admin fee

getReserves().details: Returns the reserves and the timestamp of the last block when they were updated

params._data: The encoded swap fee rate and admin fee rate
params._tokens: The addresses of the tokens in the pair

mint(address).details: Mint liquidity tokens to the caller and add corresponding reserves

params._to: The address to mint liquidity tokens to

returns._liquidity: The amount of liquidity tokens minted

permit(address,address,uint256,uint256,u.details: Approves a spender to transfer tokens on behalf of the owner, using a permit signature.

params.deadline: The deadline by which the permit must be used.
params.owner: The address of the owner of the tokens.
params.r: The R component of the permit signature.
params.s: The S component of the permit signature.
params.spender: The address of the spender to be approved.
params.v: The recovery byte of the permit signature.
params.value: The amount of tokens to be approved for transfer.

skim(address).details: Skim the excess tokens from the contract and send them to the specified address

params._to: The address to send the excess tokens to

params._amount0Out: The amount of token0 to receive
params._amount1Out: The amount of token1 to receive
params._data: Additional data with no specified format, sent in call to `_to`
params._to: The address to send the tokens to

tokens().details: Returns the tokens in the pair

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfers tokens from the caller's address to another address.

params.to: The address to which the tokens will be transferred.
params.value: The amount of tokens to be transferred.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the transfer was successful or not.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers tokens from one address to another, on behalf of the owner.

params.from: The address from which the tokens will be transferred.
params.to: The address to which the tokens will be transferred.
params.value: The amount of tokens to be transferred.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the transfer was successful or not.

devdoc.title: VolatilePair
